

class Solution {
    public ArrayList<Integer> findDuplicates(int[] arr) {
        
        ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();	                                                            // store duplicate elements
        
        int n = arr.length;			                                                                                	// length of array
        boolean visit[] = new boolean[n+1];		                                                                    // visited array (index based on value)
        
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){			                                                                                // traverse full array
            if(!visit[arr[i]]){		                                                                              	// if element not seen before
                visit[arr[i]] = true;	                                                                          	// mark as visited
            }
            else{
                list.add(arr[i]);		                                                                              // element already seen → duplicate
            }
        }
        
        return list;				                                                                                      // return duplicate list
    }
}


//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Array Duplicates:
Given an array arr[] of size n, containing elements from the range 1 to n, and each element appears at most twice, return an array of all the integers that appears twice.

Note: You can return the elements in any order but the driver code will print them in sorted order.

Examples:

Input: arr[] = [2, 3, 1, 2, 3]
Output: [2, 3] 
Explanation: 2 and 3 occur more than once in the given array.

Input: arr[] = [3, 1, 2] 
Output: []
Explanation: There is no repeating element in the array, so the output is empty.

Constraints:
1 ≤ n ≤ 106
1 ≤ arr[i] ≤ n

